inn1.comm: deflected to the off side, no run
Blistering! Ganguly backs away and swats it past the off side for a four. Oh Ah. What a peppering!
fast and straight, Gambhir blocks it
down the leg side, this is not what West Indies want. leg bye races away down the leg side for four
steered away to the off side for another single
easily done, tucked round the corner
flicked away to the short midwicket region for an easy single. West Indies just can't stop the run-flow now
taped to the off side, straight to the fielder
on the hips again, worked to backward square leg. again no run.
on a length, outside off stump, wide called. Harsh call.

inn2.comm: Short and wide, slapped past cover point. Cracking start from Chanders
Whack! slighty short, Chanders spanks it to wide long on. Chanderpaul is on fire!
overpitched, drilled to cover

huge shout for a catch behind. Shaves past the outside edge as he is beaten on the forward prod. There must have been some sound but the umpire is not convinced that it was woody. The snickometer doesn't reveal any edge
dabbed away to third man
well outside the of stump, left alone
And again
on a length, just outside off stump, pushed to cover
fullish, outside off, Chanderpaul leans forward, defends it on the front foot
fuller, on the middle and off, driven to mid-on
In the zone outside off stump, left alone
just short of length, just outside the off stump, Gayle stays back, opens the bat-face, runs it past point
on a length, just outside off, defended away to the off side
beaten! lovely probing delivery around the off stump, lands on a length, and then moves away, Gayle pushes his bat inside the line and the ball whizzes past the outside edge
Gayle loses his bat! Goes for a short-arm jab at a length delivery and after he made contact with the ball, the bat sliped out of his hands and went behind him!

crack! Fullish, outside the off stump line, Gayle flays at it, off the back foot, and the ball flies down to thirdman. Just one bounce ahead of a diving Gambhir. Valiant effort but he cant' quite reach it.
Wallop! Short of length, outside the off stump, Gayle rocks back and spanks it past point. The ball crashes into the advertising boards.
Calm after the storm! around the off stump line, pushed out to cover
this one is steered to point
Fullish, on the off stump line, Gayle brings his bat straight down the line and bisects the bowler and the mid-on
fullish, on the legs, turned to square leg

Tendulkar drops a dolly! Banged in short of length, outside the off stump, Gayle goes for a forcing shot through off side ring and the ball flies to right of Tendulkar at first slip and ends up palming it
fullish, on the legs, clipped to backward square leg
Whack! Gayle drills a fullish delivery over a leaping mid-off!
around the off stump, driven to cover
swing and a miss. Chanderpaul is standing outside the crease, tries to flay at a short of length, outside off stump but doesn't make contact
Bosh! Creamed through covers. It is raining boundaries at Nagpur. Fullish, outside off, Chanderpaul is quick to come forward and drills it through cover
around the off stump line, pushed to the off side
on the middle stump line, full in length, Chanders leans forward, drives it to mid-on
edged past the lone slip! Lands on a length, outside off stump, Chanderpaul pushes at it and the ball runs away to third man region. 43 for 0 in 7 overs.
on the leg stump line, Gayle tucks it to deep square leg. Will get a single.
that> crablike stance, then he comes side on ish, dabs a ball on the hips, past square leg/.
Short of length, on the off stump line, Gayle delivers his special. Goes back, opens up his stance and just punches it down the ground.
Boom! Fullish, outside off stump, Gayle leans forward, drills it over short cover
short of length, on the middle and leg stump line, Gayle stands tall, whips it past square leg
almost overpitched, outside off, Gayle drives to short cover

Slam! Gayle sends the white ball flying over mid-off. Right in the slot and all he had to do was to clear the mid-off and he does just that. DOesn't go left or right of him, just sends it up and over him!
just not violence, he is picking up his singles as well. outside off stump, placed to cover point
inside-edge takes the ball dangerously close to the off stump. Outside off, Chanderpaul tries to nudge it away towards point but gets a edge
The floodgates remain open! Shortish, on the hips, Gayle helps it over backward square-leg.
Agarkar tries to go for a slower ball, the ball races away to wide mid-wicket boundary as Gayle swings it away from his presence
lands on a length, on the middle and off stump line, pushed to left of mid-off and they run with the stroke
short of length, outside off stump, run down to third man
pushed to extra cover and Agarkar, who came in because Sreesanth was bleeding runs, has given away 21 runs in 2 overs. West indies are running hot here. Long long way to go though.
on the off stump line, punched to extra cover
one slip in place, this one is on the leg stump line, dabbed away towards square-leg

tough chance at first slip! Short of length, outside off stump, Chanderpaul cuts, gets a outside edge and it flies over first slip, he stretches his hand out and it just brushes his fingers and runs away to the boundary
pushed to point
floated on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
length delivery, on the off stump line, punched to mid-off
on the off stump line, hit to deep backward point
tight line, on a length, just outside off stump, pushed to the off side
29th ODI fifty! slightly short of lengthm, outside off stump and Gayle stands tall to punch it past point
short of length, outside off stump, turned to point

Beauty! Lands on the leg stump line, Gayle is turned inside out as he shapes to work it to the on side, and gets a outside edge as the ball turns and Rahul Dravid pouches a low catch at first slip. Huge wicket!
tossed up on the of fstump, pushed back to the bowler
floated on middle and leg, turned to long leg
on middle and leg, turned past square leg
short of length, dabbed away to short third man
on a length, outside off stump, nudged to the off side.
fullish, just outside the off stump, pushed to mid-off. West Indies have slowed down a touch.
short of length, run down to short thirdman
just outside off stump, pushed to point
fullish, on the off stump, driven to mid-off
goes for the flick on the on side but fails to make contact
punched away off the back-foot to the cover region, another dot ball
line and length, hint of turn and Morton forces it away towards cover point
lofted straight down the ground to the long-on region, this is turning out to be a good over for India
defended outside the off stump
punched off the back-foot to the mid-off region, easy single to end the over
good length delivery outside the off stump and Chanderpual thumps it away to the midwicket fence, fetched it from wide outside the off stump
even better! another hit across the line and this time the ball flies over the midwicket region. Sreesanth's diving effort ends in vain
pulled away, again through midwicket - just a single on this occasion. Agarkar continues to bleed runs
turned straight to the fielder at mid-wicket
Morton too joins the party! fuller length delivery , drilled straight back down the track
on the leg and middle,, pushed to mid-on and he sets off with the stroke. Drinks break.
on the middle, defended to short leg
Harbhajan nails another victim! Cleans up Morton! Drifts in on the middle stump line and straightens, Morton is beaten in the flight and by the straightening, tries to work to on side and is bowled.
pushed towards mid-off and they rush across for a single
lands on a length, outside off, comes in a touch, he jabs at it and gets a inside edge onto his inner thigh
on the middle stump, turned to the on side
pushed to the off side
full in length, on the middle stump, worked to mid-on
probing line outside the off stump, pushed to the off side. Good tight over from Agarkar. He has bounced back after the intial mauling.
on the leg and middle, worked through midwicket
comes down the track, Harbhajan drags back the length and he defends
tossed up on the middle stump line, pushed to mid-on for a single
late cut ! Just outside off stump, slightly short of length, Chanderpaul leans back, caresses it past slip.
pushed to wide mid-off for single
turns in from outside off, patted to the off side
on the hips, turned to short fine leg, Chanders wants a run but is sent back.
again on the hips, dabbed to backward squareleg
Finally he succeeds, again dabbed to backward square leg region but this time slightly wide of Zaheer and will get a single
fullish, driven to cover
dabbed to thirdman
short of length, outside off, guided to point where Karthik swoops on to the ball
shot!slightly short, Samuels rocks back and hammers it away through the gap between the cover fielders
in the channel outside off stump, Samuels has a lame poke at it and is beaten
fullish, driven to mid-on
beaten! in the corridor outside off, Samuels fishes at it open-face of the bat and the ball just teases the outside edge
Single to wide of mid-on
driven to mid-on, Samuels, at non-striker's end, sets off for a run and is sent back in time
outside off, steered to point
What a shot! Samuels charges down the track, Harbhajan pushes it outside off, Samuels wades into the line and creams it over wide long off
floated on the middle, driven to long on
tossed up on the middle stump line, driven to left of mid-on where Gambhir makes the stop
on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
And again. It was a  low full toss
cuts away after landing on the seam, around middle, Chanderpaul opens the bat-face and runs it down to point
44th ODI fifty! Short of length, outside off, punched past point. The cap comes off, the bat is raised.
on the leg and middle, worked to the on side
on the legs, flicked away to long leg
lands on a length, around off and middle stump line, pushed out to cover region
on the off stump line, punched to long on
on the leg and middle, worked to deep square leg
frm round the stumps, on the leg stump line, pushed to the on side
turns in from outside off, worked to fine leg
he is bowling seam-up. A slow leg cutter, on the off stump line, driven to long off
continues with his medium pace stuff. outside off stump, pushed to point
on the leg and middle , worked past square leg
on a length, on the off stump line, driven to Kartik at cover
outside off stump, turned to cover point
Samuels gives the charge, goes for a big heave but doesn't make contact
on the middle stump line, worked through midwicket
slower one, on the leg stump line, worked to midwicket
fullish, driven to Tendulkar at cover. who then transfers the ball from right to left and hurls a throw back at the keeper. Ambidextrous
fullish, on the off stump line, driven to mid-off. Ther required run rate has climbed above 8. No great effort from WI to up the ante.
on the off stump line, driven to mid-off
on the leg stump line, flicked away through midwicket
offspin now! lands on the off stump line, breaks away, cut to point
wide outside off stump
fullish, outside off, sliced away, one handed, over point!
driven to mid-on
full and outside off , driven to wide mid off.
low full toss, on off stump, driven to deep cover
offspin on the off stump line, driven to long on
just outside off stump, turned to gully
on the off stump, whipped to midwicket
seam-up on the off stump, driven to mid-off. Tendulkar is keeping it real tight here
outside off stump, pushed to right of Tendulkar who gets across to make the stop
innovative shotmaking there! He just walked across, took it from outside off stump and whipped it behind squareleg!
Another meaty blow! on a length and Chanders just leans forward and swings it over deep midwicket
fuller, outside off, driven to long off
on a length, around middle and off stump, whipped through midwicket
on the off stump line, nudged to extra cover for a single
outside off, full in length, driven powerfully to mid-on
way outside off stump
offspin this time, swept from outside off , to long leg
fuller, driven to long on
seam-up, quicker on the off side, pushed to point
Awesome strike! Dances down the track and sends the white ball flying over long-off
on the legs, tucked behind square leg for couple of runs
another two, similar shot, down fine leg
on the leg and middle stump line, Lara goes on a bent knee, laps it aroudn the corner but can't beat the short fine leg fielder
comes down the track, drives to long on
tossed up on the middle stump line, Chanderpaul leans forward, drives to long off
There he goes again! Waltzes down the track and backs away to the leg side in the process and heaves it over long off. THe ball lands on the roof. The full swing of the bat was a delight to watch
Ah! the whiplash drive through square point. Full and just outside off, he leant forward and sliced it past point
slightly short, pulled to midwicket
Lara comes down the track, Tendulkar drags back the length, L:ara adjusts, dabs it away towards midwicket
flat and quick, outside leg stump line, Chanderpaul sweeps it fine.
just outside off stump, short of length, cut to point
dabbed away to fine leg
just outside the off stump, cut past point where GAmbhir pulls out a awkward looking drive, lands on his knee..
pushed to short cover for a quick single
risky! He charges out and tries to play a lofted shot, beaten by the dip, gets a inside edge and it goes past the leg stump
comes down the track and hits it straight to long-off, on one bounce
Chanderpaul pings the same man, but along the ground
Lara charges out again, prior to the release, Harbhajan fires it flat and quick, outside off, Lara reaches out for it and gets a inside edge.  10 overs to go. 100 to get. Hurtling towards a thriller.
offspin, just outside off stump, waits for the ball to arrive, dabs it wide of short third man
fuller, outside off, driven to long off

Tendulkar ends Lara's knock. Anticipating that Lara would come down the track, he fires is a seam-up delivery, full and outside off stump, Lara is beaten by the pace and the length as he tries to stab at it and Dhoni pulls off a smart stumping. That is a huge wicket and tilts the scale back towards India.
outside off stump, driven past Tendulkar to long off
on the legs, turned towards midwicket for a single.
lands outside leg stump, turns in on the leg stump line, cramps up Chanders who just pushes it out to the on side
on the off stump, pushed past point
lovely delivery, on the off stump line, Bravo comes down the track, and is beaten by the doosra, and it runs him off the pads to the off side
5th ODI hundred for Chanderpaul, 2nd against India. Fullish , driven to long off.
on the middle, turned to short midwicket
swept past square leg
slightly short and Bravo eases back to pull it over midwicket
on the legs, flicked away through midwicket
fullish, dipping on the leg stump line, Chanderpaul tries to work it to on side, misses and the ball bounds away off the boot
slips down leg side and Bravo makes him pay. Picks it over midwicket
on the middle and leg, whipped to deep midwicket
slightly short of length, on the leg and middle stump line,, Bravo whips it calypso style and  Agarkar fumbles at the midwicket boundary
fullish, driven to long on
driven to cover for a single
Gone! Zaheer takes out Bravo. Lands on a length, on the off and middle stump line, slants away, Bravo tries to cut it late, is cramped up a touch and nicks it to Dhoni
fullish, on the leg and middle, tickled around the corner
giftwraps a boundary. full toss outside off, carved through backward point
full in length, on the middle stump line, driven to mid-on, the throw almost takes out Agarkar who just about evades it!
Crash! a yorker skids under the desperate wave of the bat and cleans up the furniture. India are at a touching distance from a victory here.
fullish, outside off, nudged towards point for a quick single. There is a shy but doesn't hit the bull's eyd and the batsman scampers home
outside off stump, Chanderpaul tries to work it across the line and doesn't make contact
driven to Harbhajan at long off
attempted yorker, on the legs, glanced away fine
slightly short of length, on off stump, Chanderpaul tries to flay in to the on side, doesn't time it well and the ball goes straight and hits the non-striker
on the legs, worked through midwicket
yorker length, on the leg stump line, Ramdin tries to jab it away and the ball bobs off the pads
shortish, on the middle and leg, pulled to deep square leg
Super yorker! just outside leg stump and somehow Ramdin manages to dig it out.
outside off stump, run down to thirdman
swing and a miss! Outside off stump, Chanderpaul has a mighty heave, doesn't make contact
Sreesanth drops a dolly! fullish and outside off, sliced to deep cover where Sreesanth clangs a simple chance.
attempted yorker, Chanderpaul leans forward and takes it on the full and creams it through extra cover
low full toss on the middle and leg stump line, clipped away to fine leg.
fullish, driven to long off
stand and deliver! fullish, outside off, drilled over cover.
fullish, just outside leg stump, Chanderpaul leans across, laps it around the corner. Dravid has a chat with Sreesant
More violence! This one is played inside out to widish long off. 36 in 15 balls now!
banged in short, Chanderpaul pulls it to right of Harbhajan SIngh at deep backwards square leg who makes a good stop.
Ramdin falls trying to go for a six. Again banged in short, at the body, Ramdin pulls, doesn't time it well and Gambhir moves to his left from fine leg to hold on to the catch.
slips this one down the leg side
short of length, on the off stump line, swatted away to long on

The white ball is flying everywhere. This one disappears over deep midwicket. Short of length, on the middle and he pulls it away. IT appeared as if he didnt time it well but it just kept going. Chanders has a long animated chat with Bradshaw.
fullish, driven to long on and they run hard to come back for two
fullish, outside off, sliced to point, Raina has a shy at non strikers end, misses - had he hit, Chanders would have been a goner, instead there is a overthrow . Agarkar is quite upset.
this time Raina doesn't throw! again steered to him, he just holds on to the ball.
yorker length, but outside off stump, Bradshaw has a wave at it and is beaten
shout for lbw, swinging in full, and Bradshaw is hit on the boot on the leg stump line and it runs away  towards third man. Marginal. half his foot was outside leg.

Sreesanth keeps his cool and gets a run out. Driven back to him,  he makes the stop, meanwhile Bradshaw is half-way down the track. Sreesanth doesn't throw, he runs with the ball towards the non-strikers end and beats Bradshaw
on the middle stump line, Chanders leans forward, swings it over midwicket
outside off , angling away, spanked to sweeper cover
Taylor backs away, Sreesanth hurls in a length delivery o nthe stumps, Taylor swats at it, makes contact with bottom of the bat and it rolls towards midoff
attempted yorker, on the off stump line, Chanderpaul pushes it out to cover and will take the single
Dravid pumps his fist as the fullish delivery beats the wave of the bat and nestles into Dhoni's gloves. India take the first match, three more to go.
